"Embeddings live in a <strong>1,536-dimensional</strong> space. Projecting"
" that down to 2 or 3 dimensions inevitably loses information — like "
"flattening a globe into a 2D map where some distances get distorted. Two "
"indicators may be very close in the original space but end up far apart "
"in the projection. The <strong>similarity scores</strong> shown in the "
"detail panel are always calculated in the full-dimensional space, so they"
" are accurate regardless of where dots appear on screen."
